				\begin{document}$$z$$\end{document}-score) and the normalized value of the sum of the values of the neighbors weighted by the corresponding weights. These five categories are the following:
High-High: spatial entities with high values of both variables under study
Low-Low: spatial entities with low values of both variables under study
Low–High: spatial entities of low value for the first variable and high value for the second variable under study
High-Low: spatial entities of high value for the first variable and low value for the second variable under study
